A '''rural cluster development (RCD)''' is a form of [[Subdivision (land)|residential subdivision]]. In an RCD, houses are clustered together in areas zoned for larger properties. The remainder of the land is often designated "open space". The effect is [[Land lot|tract]]-home density in the middle of [[Types of rural communities|rural communities]].<ref>[http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/pardonourdust/2008/03/green-model-h-1.html Pardon Our Dust : Los Angeles Times : Green model homes burn near Seattle; arson suspected<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

